[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Kling is a 62-year-old gentleman who underwent a low-anterior resection with end-to-end descending colorectostomy for an upper rectal and lower sigmoid carcinoma.  Pathology revealed 34 negative lymph nodes.  Mr. Kling was recently hospitalized locally for fever and weakness.  Was given some IV antibiotics and now feels much better.

[end section id="20103"]

